SIMPLE: halloo
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Halloo
<hw>Hal*loo"</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l*l⟦oomac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Perh. fr. <ets>ah</ets> + <ets>lo</ets>; cf. AS.
<ets>eal⟦amac⟧</ets>, G. <ets>halloh</ets>, F. <ets>haler</ets> to set
(a dog) on. Cf. <er>Hollo</er>, <ets>interj</ets>.]</ety> <def>A loud
exclamation; a call to invite attention or to incite a person or an
animal; a shout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>List! List! I hear⟦br⟧
Some far off <qex>halloo</qex> break the silent air.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halloo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Halloo
<hw>Hal*loo"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hallooed</conjf> <pr>(-l⟦oomac⟧d")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Hallooing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cry out; to exclaim
with a loud voice; to call to a person, as by the word
<ex>halloo</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Country folks <qex>hallooed</qex> and hooted after me.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halloo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Halloo
<hw>Hal*loo"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To encourage with
shouts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old John <qex>hallooes</qex> his hounds again.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To chase with shouts or outcries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If I fly . . . <qex>Halloo</qex> me like a hare.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To call or shout to; to hail.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halloo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Halloo
<hw>Hal*loo"</hw>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>halow</ets>. See
<er>Halloo</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>An exclamation to call
attention or to encourage one. Now mostly replaced by
<er>hello</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hallow</ent>⟦br⟧
